summary: It annoys me greatly when people complain that Sansa didn’t follow the practice of both sentencing and swinging the sword as if...
body: It annoys me greatly when people complain that Sansa didn’t follow the practice of both sentencing and swinging the sword as if Ned wasn’t the one who not only never taught her to do that but he also didn’t brought her to watch executions in the first place. In fact, the only executions she ever witnessed before Littlefinger’s were some where people she knew and cared about were unjustly murdered.  Like are y’all honestly attacking her for not doing something her parents never bothered to teach her to do.

summary: How much of Littlefinger's apparent lack of tact and social grace do you think is deliberately cultivated to put others off...
question: How much of Littlefinger's apparent lack of tact and social grace do you think is deliberately cultivated to put others off their guard? After all, how dangerous can a man who apparently doesn't understand that you really shouldn't boast about bedding your social superiors' wives be?
answer:
Littlefinger’s a classic case of thinks he’s more clever than he actually is.  

He came from nothing, so he has no real gauge on loss.  But he says it himself in Alayne I - 

“—I might have to remove her from the game sooner than I’d planned. Provided she does not remove herself first.” Petyr teased her with a little smile. “In the game of thrones, even the humblest pieces can have wills of their own. Sometimes they refuse to make the moves you’ve planned for them. Mark that well, Alayne. It’s a lesson that Cersei Lannister still has yet to learn. Now, don’t you have some duties to perform?“ 

His lack of true awareness and tact is loose and messy.  He’s not a master of the game, and it’s completely obnoxious when people claim he is the best, because he’s obviously not.  I mean, his suspension of disbelief in his abilities, alone; that same little boy who found himself wounded not only physically but also emotionally by Brandon Stark never really grew up, and he’s clung to that mentality for far too long.

So, is Littlefinger that dangerous? No, and especially not when you throw a little girl in the mix who’s been learning from the worst of the worst of the top players, and has one thing they’re lacking: empathy.

summary: Do you think Cat is a poor parent as well? (I  think she could/should have handled Mordane better.)
question: Do you think Cat is a poor parent as well? (I  think she could/should have handled Mordane better.)
answer:
Yes. But everyone already talks shit about Cat. This was about unpopular positions.

You know who also should have handled Mordane? Ned, who should have fired her ass after she passed out drunk in public when she should have been looking after her charge, the 11 year old future crown princess. Sansa was escorted home by a child murderer. Ned either did not notice or did not care.

Just like he did not care that his other daughter was running around alone in a dangerous, Lannister controlled city after said daughter was literally hunted through the woods by The Hound and Jaime Lannister over a dog bite.
